<TITLE> Tanjim returns to work </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com) - State minister for home Tanjim Ahmed returned to his office Thursday, after days of absence and reports of his resignation were widely circulated. Tanjim entered the home ministry at around 11:30am. Reluctant to talk to reporters, he said only, "I have been indisposed." Mojakker Ali, his private secretary, was seen going into the minister's office carrying official documents. Tanjim, accompanied by home minister Sahara Khatun and LGRD minister Syed Ashraful Islam, had a two-hour meeting with prime minister Sheikh Hasina at her Hare Road residence on Wednesday evening. Tanjim, popularly known as Sohel Taj, had been away from office since Sunday last, stoking the reports of his resignation. A spokesman for the minister said he was absent from his office due to "illness", not resignation. "He could not attend office due to a fever," Ruhul Amin, general secretary of Tanjim's Kapasia constituency, told reporters late Wednesday night after meeting with the state minister at the latter's Minto Road residence. He will start attending his office regularly from Thursday, said Amin. "The state minister has said he would courteously accept any directive from the prime minister," he added. Reports that Tanjim, after five months in office, had submitted his resignation grew on Monday, as he was seen was seen going into the prime minister's office after days of absence. The home minister herself had said she was unable to contact him at the time, but denied the rumours of his resignation. The media also spoke of disagreements between Sahara and Tanjim. The home minister rubbished the reports. "Tanjim is like my own son. There arises no question at all of any rifts between us." An official at the prime minister's official residence, wishing anonymity, said Tanjim had met and had discussions with the prime minister for an hour and a half on Monday evening. The next day, Sahara said Tanjim had applied for leave citing personal grounds. The home minister said she had approved his leave application from June 6 to 23 and forwarded it to the prime minister. She added that Tanjim had talked about going to the US on leave to see his wife and children there. bdnew
